  "remarks": "Igor Rudenya is the governor of Tver Oblast, appointed by President Vladimir Putin. In his role as governor, Igor Rudenya manages a regional state body of the Russian Federation and is responsible for implementing state policies at regional level. He has expressed support for the illegal recognition of the so-called independence of the so-called Donetsk and Luhansk Peoples Republics and the war of aggression against Ukraine.",
